module: a2-32
level: A2
sequence: 32
slug: which-one
version: '2.0'
title: Which One?
subtitle: Relative Clauses with Який
content_outline:
- section: Introduction / Вступ
  points:
  - 'The power of description beyond adjectives — describing people and things with
    full sentences; cultural hook: ''Який пан, такий жупан'' (Like master, like coat)
    — illustrates how ''який'' matches the noun it describes'
  - '''The Chameleon: Why ''''Який'''' is the ultimate linker'' — visual aid: ''Mirror''
    analogy (reflects noun gender/number)'
- section: Presentation / Презентація
  points:
  - '''Basic Agreement: Який, Яка, Яке, Які'' — starting with Nominative case; learner
    error: case agreement failures (mismatching gender/number with antecedent)'
  - '''The Case Detective: Why ''''Який'''' changes inside the clause'' — introducing
    Accusative forms; rule: case determined by clause verb (знаю кого? -> якого),
    not the antecedent; visual aid: ''dresses for the job inside the new sentence'''
  - '''Who vs. Which: The universal nature of ''''Який'''''' — learner error: using
    ''хто'' instead of ''який'' for people; differentiation: ''хто'' is for ''He who...''
    (Той, хто...), ''який'' modifies specific nouns'
  - '''Abstract Links: Те, що...'' — standard reference: §4.4.2 (complex sentences
    with ''що'', ''тому що'', ''щоб'')'
  - '''Precision: Defining your subject with relative clauses'' — market culture:
    ''Який вам зважити?'' (Which one do you want?), ''Які помідори найсолодші?'''
  - 'The Mandatory Comma — learner error: omitting comma before ''який'' (unlike English
    restrictive clauses)'
- section: Practice / Практика
  points:
  - Sentence merging drills — combining simple sentences into complex ones; focus
    on gender/number agreement
  - '''Wanted'' poster description exercises — describing suspects or lost items using
    ''який''; learner error: failing to decline ''який'' in Accusative (Я бачу чоловіка,
    якого...)'
- section: Dialogues / Діалоги
  points:
  - 'Police witness interview or searching for a specific item in a shop — using ''який/яка/яке''
    to specify details; context: selecting items at a market (''Selection'' culture)'
focus: grammar
pedagogy: PPP
objectives:
- Learner can use 'який' to connect sentences
- Learner can decline 'який' to match the gender and case of the noun
- Learner can describe people and objects using relative clauses
- Learner can punctuate complex sentences correctly
grammar:
- relative pronoun який (declension)
- defining relative clauses
- punctuation in complex sentences
- adjective agreement rules
module_type: grammar
sources:
- name: Ukrainian State Standard 2024 - Relative Clauses
  url: https://mon.gov.ua/
  type: reference
  notes: Standards for complex sentence structures and relative pronouns at A2
- name: Grammar of Ukrainian Language - Relative Pronouns
  url: https://uk.wikipedia.org/wiki/Відносні_займенники
  type: reference
  notes: Declension rules for 'який' and its role in subordinate clauses
immersion: 60-75% Ukrainian
phase: A2.2
persona:
  voice: Encouraging Cultural Guide
  role: Competition Judge
vocabulary_hints:
  required:
  - який (which/that/who - masc) — який це?, той, який... (the one who/which)
  - яка (which/that/who - fem) — яка різниця? (what's the difference?), дівчина, яка...
  - яке (which/that/who - neut) — яке сьогодні число? (what is the date today?)
  - які (which/that/who - pl) — люди, які... (people who...), які плани?
  - той (that one) — той, хто... (he who...), той самий (the same one)
  recommended:
  - 'чоловік (man/husband) — learner error: чоловік = man AND husband'
  - 'жінка (woman/wife) — learner error: жінка = woman AND wife'
word_target: 3000
